  "rationale": "WoodWave has no logo-wall or feature-grid vocabulary, so the SaaS-typical hero\u2192logos\u2192feature-cards\u2192testimonial\u2192cta sequence is remapped onto editorial vocabulary. The page opens with the sanctioned inverse hero bookend (hero-split-media-copy): the ONLY inverse surface, the ONLY accent (on the display title), stacking the sole legal text-on-media with the brand's primary overlap ornament. The three value_props are rendered as a NOVEL off-grid collage \u2014 one repeatable feature-item slot carrying a 3-object copy array \u2014 broken off the grid with heavy stagger and a ghost watermark (the editorial signature the library lacked as a discrete section). The gallery adapts gallery-mosaic-with-overflow (bento\u2192collage) with bleed, ghost-word and staggered frames using the only two real assets plus one renderer-supplied frame. Social proof, which WoodWave has no logo-wall for, is mapped onto a panel split pairing the 10,000+ stat with the pulled quote (the logo-wall requirement is flagged as a gap \u2014 no logo assets exist, so it is intentionally omitted rather than faked). The page closes on a centered conversion stack (centering reserved for the bookend/cta per no-centered-everything). Every non-hero section stays on primary/panel with no accent, honoring single-accent and all neverDo rules."
